2.title: Black Dude on the Ground and Pound
2.plot: Sam tells Donkey about his new vigilante job in an extremely coy manner. We meet Sam's boss at "Pension Recovery Force", Just Mel.

3.title: Submit Practice Dad
3.plot: Sam sets a date to meet Jen's dad and uses his own dad to practice his submissions. Mel drops by to congratulate Sam on his first job and to assign him his next job. Then there's confusion about Yoga terms.

4.title: Dinosaur Triangle Choke
4.plot: Jen has the boy talk at lunch with her dad (Kim Estes) and gets hit on by an odd waiter (Linc Hand). Meanwhile Sam is out on his next big job and runs into an interesting ghetto delicious in-home secretary, Ambuh' (Ashley Rideaux) along with a big rugby-esque personal security guard, Buzz Cut (Matt Iseman).

5.title: Kimura Mike Knight
5.plot: Sam's life as a neighborhood vigilante against white collar crime comes to a halt with black santa, Mike Knight. Jen and Sam's worlds collide, in a major way. Like, MAJOR! (Oh, and Ambuh' gets a half day off.) (Cotto and Chatto pretend to rake).

6.title: Rear Naked Tub Sex
6.plot: Sam faces the consequences of screwing up his second "vigilante" job in which he was double crossed.

7.title: Cuban Jabba the Hutt
7.plot: Sam deals with Jen flip flopping her attitude about him being a pro Vigilante. Sam goes to get his next job from Just Mel and is again faced with a tough decision. This episode introduces Ed Ackerman as "KJ Chalk", former heavyweight cagefighting champion. Just Mel's headquarters is hard to get to.

8.title: Superman Punch the Clown
8.plot: After Sam gets handed a hit job that forces him to take out a woman, Jessica Steinman, he decides this is a chance for him to win back Jen by getting her involved in Pension Recovery Force. A random clown accidentally sets off Sam then gets involved. Then something goes wrong.

9.title: Overhand Right, Right?!
9.plot: Jen and Sam awkwardly try to complete Sam's next vigilante job which puts Jen into a situation that she doesn't enjoy - at all. We also find out how Sam and Jen first met.

10.title: Hit Her Button
10.plot: Watch Jen knock out another bitch... Jessica Steinman. Get a glimpse of Sam and his brother, Ronnie as kids. And something major happens in the Sam/Jen engagement.

11.title: Hammerfist, Knee, Guillotine Fiend
11.plot: Now that Jen and Sam have broken up, it's time to see how they each react. Fight or Flight for the relationship? Jen gets an idea from her friend, Katie, as to what to do about Sam. Meanwhile, Sam decides to bury his head into his work and makes rushed demands on Mel to give him another hit job.

12.title: Full Mount on the Mount
12.plot: Sam deals with losing his relationship with Jen by going to Mel, his vigilante boss, and forcing him to hurriedly give him another hit. Mel doesn't have all the details of the targets, which leads Sam into a trap. The biggest trap of his life. Jen also deals with an internal struggle of whether to turn in both her step-father and Sam to the authorities, Detective O'Hayes. Det. O'Hayes mounts his longtime investigation, and stumbles upon Sam's vigilante ways on an unlikely mountain top with his two crooked partners. Sam finds himself faced with these two crooked cops, ...

imdb.plot outline: In the United States, somebody gets screwed-over every day in some manner. Pension funds are squandered by CEO's, investment opportunities turn up false, and on and on... The consequences are; the common man (mankind) gets screwed out of their hard earned dollar, and their perpetrators are left unpunished or slapped on the wrist. Well, what if those perpetrators were punished with physical pain and/or death?... What if Bernie Madoff woke up in his cell every day, not with his normal face in the mirror, but a face that's riddled with scars. His bones and joints ache from being shattered. That's what our main character, Sam Bransby, does... That's what "Pension Recovery Force" does!
imdb.title: Choke.Kick.Girl: The Series
plot: Sam Bransby watches cage fighting, and uses the fight skills to recoup his dad's stolen pension under the direction of hitBoss, Mel, in their group, "Pension Recovery Force". It gets ugly when the love of his life Jen gets involved.::Ryan Churchill
